 242:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c **** /**
 243:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  * @brief  Data received over USB OUT endpoint are sent over CDC interface
 244:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  *         through this function.
 245:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  *
 246:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  *         @note
 247:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  *         This function will issue a NAK packet on any OUT packet received on
 248:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  *         USB endpoint until exiting this function. If you exit this function
 249:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  *         before transfer is complete on CDC interface (ie. using DMA
 250:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  * controller) it will result in receiving more data while previous ones are
 251:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  * still not sent.
 252:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  *
 253:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  * @param  Buf: Buffer of data to be received
 254:USB_Device/App/usbd_cdc_if.c ****  * @param  Len: Number of data received (in bytes)
